The @fig-normal shows a normal distribution.

```{r}
#| label: fig-normal
#| fig-cap: a normal distribution
x= seq(-3,3, length.out=10000)
dx= dnorm(x)
plot(x, dx, type= "l", cex=2, lwd=3)
```

@fig-normalProperties illustrates the different kinds of normal distribution and we have:
(Density)@fig-normalProperties-1, 
(Cumulative)@fig-normalProperties-2 and 
(Quantile)@fig-normalProperties-3



```{r}
#| layout-ncol: 3
#| label: fig-normalProperties
#| fig-cap: Normal distribution
#| fig-subcap: 
#|   - "Density"
#|   - "Cumulative"
#|   - "Quantile"
plot(x, dx, type= "l", cex=2, lwd=3)
plot(x, pnorm(x), type= "l", cex=2, lwd=3)
plot(pnorm(x), qnorm(pnorm(x)), type= "l", cex=2, lwd=3)
```



